The paper deals with the relationship between communication complexity and algorithmic entropy, which are both fundamental concepts in theoretical computer science. The use of oracles and the focus on instance complexity suggest a connection to complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of information theory and entropy measures suggest a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The study of sets and values also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the study of complexity measures and their relationships suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
